{
  "stem": "8359.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he was getting rid of some Jews, sent them into Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they would tells us that what's going in Germany, how they hate the Jews, and how they take away their homes, their businesses, how they literally kill them, whatever they do.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know whether we really-- well, we did believe it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because why would people--?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The German Jew-- Jews as a rule, to my knowledge, they were pretty successful.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Why would they just all of a sudden pick up and leave homeland, a land that they were born, their kids were-- How did the Jews in your town react to these stories?",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "People didn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the whole thing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They settled, like I say, in our town, the Katowice.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "See, that was basically-- this-- this part of Poland, I think during World War I or before, it was part of Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they still, some of the state, not the Jews, but I mean, the non-Jews, they spoke German.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, so it was easier for them to live there, because they like walked from one, you know, into something that are was easier for them to settle in.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm sure there were, but the to be honest with you, I was too young to pay attention to this stuff.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was at home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I happened to be up six o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Was a beautiful, glorious day.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The sun was shining.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I heard the plane overhead, looked up, and Hitler attacked Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I saw the plane.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't see any bombing or anything like this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I heard the-- like shots, like maybe they were-- the Polish army-- that was another joke.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
